data.title: German Titov
data.meta_description: German Titov. Actor: Slike sveta. German Titov was born on 11 September 1935 in Verkhneye Zhilino, West Siberian Krai, RSFSR, USSR [now Altai Krai, Russia]. He was an actor, known for Slike sveta (1962), Stan niewazkosci (1994) and Our World (1986). He died on 20 September 2000 in Moscow, Russia.
data.text:
Piloted the Vostok 2 spacecraft on 6 August 1961, becoming the first man to orbit the earth multiple times. He also became the second Russian (after fellow cosmonaut Yuri Gagarin) and the fourth human (after Gagarin and American astronauts Alan Shepard and Gus Grissom) to enter space.

Dear Muscovites, there are no changes in the cabin. The pressure is normal, perfect pressure ... I am perfectly comfortable. I wish you the same. [said as Vostok II passed over Moscow]
